#: _versions/3.15/guides/reactive-routes.adoc
msgid "Using Reactive Routes"
msgstr "Usando rotas reativas"

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.15/guides/reactive-routes.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Reactive routes propose an alternative approach to implement HTTP endpoints where you declare and chain _routes_.\n"
"This approach became very popular in the JavaScript world, with frameworks like Express.Js or Hapi.\n"
"Quarkus also offers the possibility to use reactive routes.\n"
"You can implement REST API with routes only or combine them with Jakarta REST resources and servlets."
msgstr "As rotas reativas propûçem uma abordagem alternativa para implementar pontos de extremidade HTTP em que o usuûÀrio declara e encadeia _rotas_ . Essa abordagem tornou-se muito popular no mundo do JavaScript, com estruturas como Express.Js ou Hapi. O Quarkus tambûˋm oferece a possibilidade de usar rotas reativas. O senhor pode implementar a API REST somente com rotas ou combinûÀ-las com recursos e servlets Jakarta REST."

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.15/guides/reactive-routes.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "The code presented in this guide is available in this {quickstarts-base-url}[GitHub repository] under the link:{quickstarts-tree-url}/reactive-routes-quickstart[`reactive-routes-quickstart` directory]"
msgstr "O cû°digo apresentado neste guia estûÀ disponûÙvel neste {quickstarts-base-url}[repositû°rio do GitHub] no link:{quickstarts-tree-url}/reactive-routes-quickstart[diretû°rioreactive-routes-quickstart]"

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.15/guides/reactive-routes.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Reactive Routes were initially introduced to provide a reactive execution model for HTTP APIs on top of the xref:quarkus-reactive-architecture.adoc[Quarkus Reactive Architecture].\n"
"With the introduction of xref:rest.adoc[Quarkus REST (formerly RESTEasy Reactive)], you can now implement reactive HTTP APIs and still use Jakarta REST annotations.\n"
"Reactive Routes are still supported, especially if you want a more _route-based_ approach, and something closer to the underlying reactive engine."
msgstr "As rotas reativas foram inicialmente introduzidas para fornecer um modelo de execuûÏûÈo reativa para APIs HTTP sobre a xref:quarkus-reactive-architecture.adoc[arquitetura reativa do Quarkus] . Com a introduûÏûÈo do xref:rest.adoc[Quarkus REST (anteriormente RESTEasy Reactive)] , agora o senhor pode implementar APIs HTTP reativas e ainda usar anotaûÏûçes Jakarta REST. As rotas reativas ainda sûÈo suportadas, especialmente se o senhor quiser uma abordagem mais _baseada em rotas_ e algo mais prû°ximo do mecanismo reativo subjacente."

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/3.15/guides/reactive-routes.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Quarkus HTTP"
msgstr "Quarkus HTTP"

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.15/guides/reactive-routes.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Before going further, let's have a look at the HTTP layer of Quarkus.\n"
"Quarkus HTTP support is based on a non-blocking and reactive engine (Eclipse Vert.x and Netty).\n"
"All the HTTP requests your application receive are handled by _event loops_ (I/O Thread) and then are routed towards the code that manages the request.\n"
"Depending on the destination, it can invoke the code managing the request on a worker thread (Servlet, Jax-RS) or use the IO Thread (reactive route).\n"
"Note that because of this, a reactive route must be non-blocking or explicitly declare its blocking nature (which would result by being called on a worker thread)."
msgstr "Antes de prosseguir, vamos dar uma olhada na camada HTTP do Quarkus. O suporte HTTP do Quarkus ûˋ baseado em um mecanismo reativo e sem bloqueio (Eclipse Vert.x e Netty). Todas as solicitaûÏûçes HTTP que o aplicativo recebe sûÈo tratadas por _loops de eventos_ (I/O Thread) e, em seguida, sûÈo encaminhadas para o cû°digo que gerencia a solicitaûÏûÈo. Dependendo do destino, ele pode invocar o cû°digo que gerencia a solicitaûÏûÈo em um thread de trabalho (Servlet, Jax-RS) ou usar o IO Thread (rota reativa). Observe que, por causa disso, uma rota reativa deve ser nûÈo bloqueante ou declarar explicitamente sua natureza bloqueante (o que resultaria em ser chamada em um thread de trabalho)."

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.15/guides/reactive-routes.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "image:http-architecture.png[alt=Quarkus HTTP Architecture]"
msgstr "image:http-architecture.png[alt=\"Quarkus HTTP Architecture\"]"

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.15/guides/reactive-routes.adoc
